citation.case_name: Wayne v. Santa Clara Valley Transportation Authority

html_with_citations:
543 U.S. 954

WAYNE
v.
SANTA CLARA VALLEY TRANSPORTATION AUTHORITY.

No. 04-5990.

Supreme Court of United States.

November 1, 2004.

1

C. A. 9th Cir. Motion of petitioner for leave to proceed in forma pauperis denied. Petitioner is allowed until November 22, 2004, within which to pay the docketing fee required by Rule 38(a) and to submit a petition in compliance with Rule 33.1 of the Rules of this Court.
